<s> Of course, Jeffrey Mogul is correct that at least in part this really a URI issue in that there is no Content-ID scheme which will allow us to implement caching at this level of granularity.  </s>
<s> Something off the top of my head (which probably means it has a lot of associated problems) is that complex objects could be encoded using external-body components with HTTP as the access method.  </s>
