<s> I think in the current web architecture, the granularity of caching is exactly 'what can be pointed to by a URL', and if you want to deliver a database record and cache some parts and not others, what you'd do is deliver a composite object that explicitly includes the other parts.  </s>
<s> If you want to use 'multipart/related' for the container, that's fine, but you might find each part being delivered as 'message/external-body;access-type=URL".  </s>
